description:
This is a record of my stroll around the coastline of Kent.

Among coastal walkers, there is a convention that you set your personal ‘rules’ as to what you consider to be ‘the coastline’. This is not as simple as you might imagine. Do you include islands? Or river estuaries? And some stretches are just not accessible due to industrial use or firing ranges for example.

So, for me, I’m generally trying to keep the sea in view wherever possible, and only going where I can reach on foot…
